    "body" : "<p>as in javascript:</p>\n\n<pre><code>mydata.match(/'([^']+)'/)[1]\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>the actual regexp is: <code>/'([^']+)'/</code></p>\n\n<p>if you use the non greedy modifier (as per another post) it's like this:</p>\n\n<pre><code>mydata.match(/'(.*?)'/)[1]\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>it is cleaner.</p>\n"
