      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "No. group(0) has special meaning, capturing groups start at index group(1)  (i.e. group(1) is correct in the answer).   &quot;Capturing groups are indexed from left to right, starting at one. Group zero denotes the entire pattern&quot; - Source: <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/regex/Matcher.html#group-int-\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/regex/&hellip;</a>"
