      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "@Elikill58 That&#39;s actually pretty clever. <code>.*&#39;</code> matches everything before the first <code>&#39;</code>, including, and <code>&#39;.*</code> matches everything else afterwards. <code>(.*?)</code> is a group that captures everything between the ticks non-greedily, I think.  <code>$1</code> means that we want to replace what was matched by the regexp (everything in this case) by contents of the first capture group (<code>(.*?)</code> that matches everything between ticks). <code>$0</code> would have meant the whole regexp."
    } ],
